1
00:00:02,100 --> 00:00:03,180
Instructor: Before we work on

2
00:00:03,180 --> 00:00:04,440
placing the order,

3
00:00:04,440 --> 00:00:05,700
let me walk you through

4
00:00:05,700 --> 00:00:07,320
the order status management

5
00:00:07,320 --> 00:00:10,620
of what happens when an order is placed,

6
00:00:10,620 --> 00:00:12,753
how the status will be updated.

7
00:00:13,770 --> 00:00:16,410
So first, what will happen is when a customer

8
00:00:16,410 --> 00:00:18,030
places an order,

9
00:00:18,030 --> 00:00:20,340
they will have to make a payment.

10
00:00:20,340 --> 00:00:21,840
Before they make a payment,

11
00:00:21,840 --> 00:00:24,150
the order status will be pending,

12
00:00:24,150 --> 00:00:27,090
and payment status will be pending.

13
00:00:27,090 --> 00:00:29,190
Once the payment is successful

14
00:00:29,190 --> 00:00:31,530
on the order confirmation page,

15
00:00:31,530 --> 00:00:34,140
the order status will be approved,

16
00:00:34,140 --> 00:00:37,653
and the payment status will also be approved.

17
00:00:38,490 --> 00:00:41,850
After that, admin will start processing the order

18
00:00:41,850 --> 00:00:44,010
so the order status will be updated

19
00:00:44,010 --> 00:00:45,210
to processing,

20
00:00:45,210 --> 00:00:49,020
but payment status always stays at approved

21
00:00:49,020 --> 00:00:51,000
once it is approved.

22
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,560
when the order is shipped,

23
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:55,170
the status will be updated to shipped,

24
00:00:55,170 --> 00:00:59,010
and payment status will remain as approved.

25
00:00:59,010 --> 00:01:01,560
Now this is the flow that we have

26
00:01:01,560 --> 00:01:04,800
for a customer placing an order,

27
00:01:04,800 --> 00:01:06,060
but in our website,

28
00:01:06,060 --> 00:01:08,340
we also have another scenario

29
00:01:08,340 --> 00:01:11,373
where a company user is placing an order.

30
00:01:12,720 --> 00:01:15,390
When a company user places an order,

31
00:01:15,390 --> 00:01:17,730
they do not have to make any payment

32
00:01:17,730 --> 00:01:19,590
because they will have 30 days

33
00:01:19,590 --> 00:01:21,360
to make the payment.

34
00:01:21,360 --> 00:01:22,800
So they will directly land

35
00:01:22,800 --> 00:01:25,020
on the order confirmation page,

36
00:01:25,020 --> 00:01:27,810
and they will see their status as approved,

37
00:01:27,810 --> 00:01:30,270
and payment status will be approved

38
00:01:30,270 --> 00:01:31,803
for delayed payment.

39
00:01:32,970 --> 00:01:34,980
Next status will be processing,

40
00:01:34,980 --> 00:01:38,880
which is same and shipped that is also same,

41
00:01:38,880 --> 00:01:41,010
but the payment status for all of them

42
00:01:41,010 --> 00:01:44,400
will be approved for delayed payment.

43
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:47,520
Then let's say after 10 days or 20 days,

44
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:50,310
whenever the company makes a payment,

45
00:01:50,310 --> 00:01:51,180
at that point,

46
00:01:51,180 --> 00:01:55,650
that payment status will be updated to approve,

47
00:01:55,650 --> 00:01:58,080
and company user will have 30 days

48
00:01:58,080 --> 00:02:01,803
to make the payment after the order is shipped.

49
00:02:02,730 --> 00:02:04,440
So that is the default flow

50
00:02:04,440 --> 00:02:08,280
that we will have when we are placing an order.

51
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:09,840
If it is a customer,

52
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:12,420
they will be navigated to make a payment.

53
00:02:12,420 --> 00:02:14,010
If it is a company,

54
00:02:14,010 --> 00:02:16,650
their status will directly be approved,

55
00:02:16,650 --> 00:02:19,440
and the payment status will be approved

56
00:02:19,440 --> 00:02:20,883
for delayed payment.

57
00:02:21,870 --> 00:02:24,510
Now all of these order status here,

58
00:02:24,510 --> 00:02:27,300
rather than having them in a magic string,

59
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:29,100
it makes sense to add them

60
00:02:29,100 --> 00:02:31,113
to the static detail file.

61
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:34,470
So let me switch back here,

62
00:02:34,470 --> 00:02:37,230
and navigate to static details,

63
00:02:37,230 --> 00:02:38,640
and I will be creating

64
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:41,790
all the constant right here.

65
00:02:41,790 --> 00:02:45,540
I have added the constant for order status here,

66
00:02:45,540 --> 00:02:48,033
and here we have the payment status.

67
00:02:49,110 --> 00:02:50,550
With that configured,

68
00:02:50,550 --> 00:02:53,253
let me continue from the next video.

